Share this on WhatsAppPresident Muhammadu Buhari will again leave Ngeria for the UK for the second time in three months.
The presidency said it is for a scheduled medical follow-up in London.
In a brief statement issued by Special Adviser on Media and Publicity,  Femi Adesina, said the President next month.
“President Muhammadu Buhari will proceed to London, the United Kingdom on Friday, June 25, 2021, for a scheduled medical follow-up.
“He is due back in the country during the second week of July, 2021,” the statement said.
The last time Buhari went for such medical check-up, some Nigerians abroad moilised and heckled him almost throughout his stay in the Nigeria House.
